name: RespiratoryProceduresI10
title: Respiratory Procedures I10
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values contains respiratory procedures most commonly used for newborns.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify newborns who have a respiratory procedure performed. Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element will map to the "Procedure" category.),(Inclusion Criteria: Codes representing the ICD-10 code system for respiratory procedures),(Exclusion Criteria: None.)
